<br>


<p>If a student tries to submit with questions not answered, a warning box will display to notify the student that they have not yet <br>completed the test (finish answering all the questions).

<p>When the warning displays, a student can either acknowledge they left the question blank on purpose and submit (clicking <br><tt>Submit Anyway</tt> on the warning pop up) or they can finish up the test by selecting <tt>Okay</tt> on the pop up warning.

<p>If a studen desires to complete the test (by clicking <tt>Okay</tt> on the warning popup), question(s) they have missed will be <br>highlited yellow to help students to locate the unanswered question(s).
	Figure 5.2.
